During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs discussed various topics, including the President's push for a broad climate bill, BP's plan to offset the cost of the oil spill against its taxes, the President's plans to reach out to the new CEO of BP, the war funding in Afghanistan, the leak of classified information by WikiLeaks, the extension of the Bush tax cuts, and the President's upcoming campaign events and fundraisers. Gibbs also addressed questions about missing funds in Iraq reconstruction and the recent slide in the President's approval ratings among different groups.